-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">d.<\/span><span> Resuspend cell pellet in <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of R10 and count cells. <\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">e. <\/span><span>Rest cells at least 3 hours (up to overnight) at 2x10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">6 <\/span><span>cells\/mL in R10 medium + 1 \u00b5L\/mL DNAse I at <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span> , 5% CO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">\u00b2<\/span><span>.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;\">Note:<\/span><span> during resting, prepare  antibody cocktail master mix. Adjust volume of ECS for <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> per test with FACS buffer.<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">f.<\/span><span> After resting, add PBS up to <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> or <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> (whichever is closer, rounding up) to cells and transfer to <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> or <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> conical tube.<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">g. <\/span><span>Spin cells at 500 xg for 5 minutes at room temperature (RT).<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">h.<\/span><span> Resuspend cells in PBS to 1x10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">7<\/span><span> cells\/mL and count. If cells are too dilute, re-spin cells and resuspend at 1x10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">7<\/span><span> cells\/mL. Transfer <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span> of cells (2x10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">6<\/span><span>cells) into each well of a V-bottom 96 well plate.<\/span><\/div><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"741EE650C7CC11EBA7E5FB973682DA72","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{