724,"guid":"29FD80F4BDB3400085095F81FFCBC908","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Viability and extracellular staining (ECS)<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">a. <\/span><span>Spin plate at 500 xg for 5  minutes at RT<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">b.<\/span><span> Using a multichannel pipette, carefully remove the supernatant.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">c.<\/span><span> Using a multichannel pipette, add <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of PBS to well.<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">d.<\/span><span> Add <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of 1:60 Aqua viability dye directly to cell pellet and resuspend cells.<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">e.<\/span><span> Incubate for 10 minutes at RT in the dark.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">f.<\/span><span> Add <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of ECS antibody cocktail to cells and incubate for 20 minutes at RT in the dark (prepare 1% PFA fixation buffer in the meantime).<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">g.<\/span><span> Add <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of FACS buffer to each well and spin plate at 500 xg for 5 minutes. <\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">h.<\/span><span> Discard supernatant and fix cells with <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of 1% PFA.<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">i.<\/span><span> Run samples on flow cytometer.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"724B3E10D9AF11EBA7D6CB2E5BD48529","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":45,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"57EE84B0C86A11EBB9321F7E645E07F6","order_id":3,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":5,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"69C970F0C86A11EBB9321F7E645E07F6","order_id":4,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":50,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"7D3A8D90C86A11EBB9321F7E645E07F6","order_id":5,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":100,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054729,"guid":"8C47B3D0C86A11EBB9321F7E645E07F6","order_id":6,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":200,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">High-parameter flow cytometry enables identification and characterization of a wide range of cell populations within a biological sample. Analysis of cell-surface epitopes using a collection of fluorophore-labeled antibodies, or extracellular stain (ECS), sufficiently labels population-identifying markers for further analysis with flow cytometry. Importantly, ECS can be applied to cryo-preserved cell suspensions recovered in tissue culture media, enabling samples to be conveniently analyzed after collection and proper cryopreservation. However, consistent cryopreserved sample recovery and ECS procedures are critical to data comparison across multiple experiments. Herein, we describe a standardized protocol for cryopreserved sample recovery and ECS procedures for cell-surface epitope labeling. <\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1627074494}